### Phase 7 — Reports & Analytics smoke tests (BR-6, PM-only)
### Prereqs: backend on http://localhost:8080 with seeded users (pm/ba/emp).
### Run top-to-bottom in IntelliJ or VSCode REST Client; variables {{pmToken}},
### {{baToken}}, {{empToken}}, {{goalId}} are captured via response handlers.

@host = http://localhost:8080

### 1. PM login
# @name pmLogin
POST {{host}}/api/v1/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{"username": "pm", "password": "pmPass1!"}

> {% client.global.set("pmToken", response.body.token); %}

### 2. BA login
# @name baLogin
POST {{host}}/api/v1/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{"username": "ba", "password": "baPass1!"}

> {% client.global.set("baToken", response.body.token); %}

### 3. EMPLOYEE login
# @name empLogin
POST {{host}}/api/v1/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{"username": "emp", "password": "empPass1!"}

> {% client.global.set("empToken", response.body.token); %}

### 4. Seed an ACTIVE goal so reports are non-empty → 201
# @name createGoal
POST {{host}}/api/v1/goals
Authorization: Bearer {{pmToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "title": "Цель для отчётов",
  "periodStart": "2026-01-01",
  "periodEnd": "2026-12-31",
  "priority": "HIGH",
  "kpis": [{"name": "Выручка", "targetValue": 1000, "currentValue": 250, "unit": "руб."}]
}

> {% client.global.set("goalId", response.body.id); %}

### 5. Submit → ACTIVE so tasks may be created on it
POST {{host}}/api/v1/goals/{{goalId}}/submit
Authorization: Bearer {{pmToken}}

### 6. Activate the goal
POST {{host}}/api/v1/goals/{{goalId}}/status
Authorization: Bearer {{pmToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{"status": "ACTIVE"}

### 7. PM creates a task on the active goal → 201
POST {{host}}/api/v1/tasks
Authorization: Bearer {{pmToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{"title": "Задача для отчётов", "description": "d", "goalId": "{{goalId}}", "priority": "HIGH"}

### 8. PM — overview (analytics header) → 200 JSON
GET {{host}}/api/v1/reports/overview
Authorization: Bearer {{pmToken}}

### 9. PM — goals progress → 200 JSON (rows[].percent)
GET {{host}}/api/v1/reports/goals-progress
Authorization: Bearer {{pmToken}}

### 10. PM — goals progress CSV → 200 text/csv; attachment
GET {{host}}/api/v1/reports/goals-progress?format=csv
Authorization: Bearer {{pmToken}}

### 11. PM — KPI progress → 200 JSON
GET {{host}}/api/v1/reports/kpis-progress
Authorization: Bearer {{pmToken}}

### 12. PM — KPI progress CSV → 200 text/csv
GET {{host}}/api/v1/reports/kpis-progress?format=csv
Authorization: Bearer {{pmToken}}

### 13. PM — task workload (assignee × status) → 200 JSON
GET {{host}}/api/v1/reports/task-workload
Authorization: Bearer {{pmToken}}

### 14. PM — overdue tasks → 200 JSON
GET {{host}}/api/v1/reports/overdue-tasks
Authorization: Bearer {{pmToken}}

### 15. PM — backlog throughput → 200 JSON
GET {{host}}/api/v1/reports/backlog-throughput
Authorization: Bearer {{pmToken}}

### 16. BA — overview → 403
GET {{host}}/api/v1/reports/overview
Authorization: Bearer {{baToken}}

### 17. BA — goals progress → 403
GET {{host}}/api/v1/reports/goals-progress
Authorization: Bearer {{baToken}}

### 18. EMPLOYEE — overview → 403
GET {{host}}/api/v1/reports/overview
Authorization: Bearer {{empToken}}

### 19. EMPLOYEE — overdue tasks CSV → 403
GET {{host}}/api/v1/reports/overdue-tasks?format=csv
Authorization: Bearer {{empToken}}

### 20. Unauthenticated — any report → 401
GET {{host}}/api/v1/reports/overview
